# 📋 OTax E-Invoice — Changes Report
**Date:** March 1, 2026  
**Session:** Full-day development & debugging session  
**Prepared for:** Team review

---

## 🎯 Executive Summary

This session focused on resolving critical issues blocking the cloud deployment cycle: JWT authentication failures, database constraint violations, missing issuer configuration, and data storage gaps between the legacy and new SaaS table systems. The OTax Signing Agent was also upgraded to v2.1.0.

---

## 🔧 Changes Made

### 1. JWT Token Storage Fix

**Files Changed:** [App.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/App.tsx)

**Problem:** Multiple frontend pages ([Settings.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/pages/Settings.tsx), [InvoiceExcel.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/pages/InvoiceExcel.tsx), [TokenSignatureSettings.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/components/TokenSignatureSettings.tsx)) read the JWT from `localStorage.getItem('token')`, but this key was **never set**. The token was only stored inside the `invoice_user` JSON object. This caused `401 Unauthorized` errors on:
- `GET /api/signing/method`
- `GET /api/signing/agent-status`
- `POST /api/eta/test-connection`

**Fix:**
```diff
// In handleLogin():
+ localStorage.setItem('token', u.token);

// In handleLogout():
+ localStorage.removeItem('token');
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Users must **log out and log back in** after this deployment for the fix to take effect.

---

### 2. Null HWID Constraint Fix

**Files Changed:** [server.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts) (settings/save endpoint)

**Problem:** Users created via the new SaaS signup flow don't have a hardware ID (`hwid`). The `clients_info_new` table uses `@@id([hwid, uid, propertyName])` — a composite primary key that requires `hwid` to be non-null. This caused:
```
null value in column 'hwid' violates not-null constraint
```

**Fix:** Auto-generate an `hwid` for cloud users when it's null:
```typescript
let hwid = hwidResult.rows[0].hwid;
if (!hwid) {
    hwid = 'CLOUD-' + Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9).toUpperCase();
    await client.query(
        `UPDATE "LoginDb".credentials SET hwid = $1 WHERE id = $2`,
        [hwid, userId]
    );
}
```

---

### 3. Test Connection — Body Credentials Fallback

**Files Changed:**
- [etaRoutes.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/routes/etaRoutes.ts) (test-connection endpoint)
- [Settings.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/pages/Settings.tsx)

**Problem:** `POST /api/eta/test-connection` returned 500 because it reads credentials from `organization_settings`, which was empty (previous save failures prevented credentials from being stored).

**Fix — Backend:** The test-connection endpoint now accepts `{ clientId, clientSecret, env }` in the request body as a fallback:
```typescript
router.post('/test-connection', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
    let service;
    try {
        const result = await getETAServiceForUser(req);
        service = result.service;
    } catch (orgErr) {
        // Fallback: use credentials from request body
        const { clientId, clientSecret, env } = req.body || {};
        if (clientId && clientSecret) {
            service = new ETAService(0, { clientId, clientSecret, environment });
        } else {
            throw orgErr;
        }
    }
    const result = await service.testConnection();
    res.json(result);
});
```

**Fix — Frontend:** [Settings.tsx](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/E-Invoice/pages/Settings.tsx) now sends the credentials in the test-connection request body.

---

### 4. Issuer Configuration — Organization Table Fallback

**Files Changed:** [server.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts) (excel/submit endpoint)

**Problem:** The `/api/excel/submit` endpoint reads issuer data (Tax ID, Company Name, Governate, Street) from `clients_info_new` properties. SaaS users store this data in the `organizations` table instead, causing:
```
Issuer configuration incomplete:
Issuer ID (Tax Registration Number) is missing.
Issuer Name (Company Name) is missing.
Issuer Governate is missing.
Issuer Street is missing.
```

**Fix:** Added organization data fallback:
```typescript
// Load organization data
const orgQuery = `
    SELECT o.* FROM "LoginDb".organizations o
    JOIN "LoginDb".credentials c ON c.organization_id = o.id
    WHERE c.id = $1`;
const orgRes = await client.query(orgQuery, [userId]);
if (orgRes.rows.length > 0) orgData = orgRes.rows[0];

// Use org data as fallback for issuer fields
const issuerData = {
    id: getProp('issuer_id') || orgData?.tax_id || '',
    name: getProp('issuer_name') || orgData?.name || '',
    governate: getProp('issuer_governorate') || orgData?.governorate || '',
    street: getProp('issuer_street') || orgData?.street || '',
    buildingNumber: getProp('issuer_buildingNumber') || orgData?.building_number || '0',
    // ... etc
};
```

---

### 5. JWT Extraction from Authorization Header

**Files Changed:** [server.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts) (excel/submit endpoint)

**Problem:** The `/api/excel/submit` only read `X-User-ID` from headers. The SaaS frontend sends `Authorization: Bearer <token>` instead, causing `userId` to be undefined.

**Fix:** Extract userId from JWT when `X-User-ID` is absent:
```typescript
let userId = req.headers['x-user-id'] as string;
if (!userId) {
    const authHeader = req.headers.authorization;
    if (authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {
        const decoded = jwt.verify(authHeader.replace('Bearer ', ''), JWT_SECRET);
        userId = String(decoded.userId);
    }
}
```

---

### 6. Dual-Write to Org-Specific Tables

**Files Changed:** [server.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts) (excel/submit endpoint)

**Problem:** After successful ETA submission, documents were only saved to `public.documents`. The org-specific tables (`"InvoicesDb".org_5_operatives_documents`) remained empty, causing the new dashboard and search features to show no data.

**Fix:** After saving to `public.documents`, also save to the org table:
```typescript
if (orgData) {
    const orgTables = getOrgTableNames(orgData.id, orgData.name);
    await createOrgTables(pool, orgData.id, orgData.name);
    await client.query(`
        INSERT INTO "InvoicesDb"."${orgTables.documents}" (...)
        ON CONFLICT (uuid) DO UPDATE SET status = EXCLUDED.status, synced_at = NOW()
    `, [...]);
}
```

---

### 7. OTax Signing Agent v2.1.0

**Files Changed:** [agent.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/agent/agent.ts)

**Enhancements Applied:**

| Feature | Before (v2.0) | After (v2.1.0) |
|---------|---------------|-----------------|
| **Concurrent signing** | Shared temp files → race condition | Unique temp dir per request (`temp/{reqId}/`) |
| **Signer validation** | None — fails silently at first sign | Pre-validates all DLLs on startup |
| **Version reporting** | Not reported | Sent in `register_agent` + heartbeat |
| **Memory monitoring** | Not tracked | `memoryMB` sent in heartbeat |
| **Temp cleanup** | Files left on disk | Auto-deleted after each sign request |
| **Platform info** | Not sent | OS/version sent during registration |

