## 🐛 Known Remaining Issues

### 1. Background ETA Sync Error
```
Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'docs')
```
The legacy [getAllETADocuments](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts#2067-2335) sync function has a bug where `syncCache[userId]` is not initialized with a `docs` array before being accessed. This is a **server-side** issue broadcast to all WebSocket clients (including the agent).

**Impact:** Low — only affects the legacy dashboard sync, not invoice submission.
**Fix needed in:** [server.ts](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts) → [getAllETADocuments()](file:///e:/app/OTax%20New%20App/backend-service/server/server.ts#2067-2335) function — ensure `syncCache[userId].docs` is initialized as `[]`.

### 2. JWT Malformed in Agent Logs
The agent receives `"jwt malformed"` errors broadcast by the server. These come from the frontend polling `/api/signing/method` and `/api/signing/agent-status` with a null token.

**Impact:** Resolved after users log out and log back in (token will be stored correctly).

